# Example .npmrc Configuration for Users
# Copy this to .npmrc and configure based on your needs

# ===================================================================
# OPTION 1: Use npm public registry (default)
# ===================================================================
# No configuration needed! Just:
# npm install @ce-dot-net/ace-client

# ===================================================================
# OPTION 2: Use GitHub Packages
# ===================================================================
# Uncomment these lines to use GitHub Packages:

# @ce-dot-net:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}

# Then set your GitHub token:
# export GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxx

# ===================================================================
# OPTION 3: Use both (npm fallback to GitHub Packages)
# ===================================================================
# Try npm first, use GitHub Packages for @ce-dot-net scope:

# @ce-dot-net:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}

# Default registry stays npm for other packages
# registry=https://registry.npmjs.org
